content.text:
**Changes Applied**
- `apps/floating-panel/src/main/index.mts`: Added resilient logging (falls back to `/tmp/webauto-floating-panel.log` on `EIO`), enabled resizing with `electron-window-state` so the window remembers its bounds, and made the window resizable with sensible minimums and state management.
- `apps/floating-panel/scripts/build.mjs`: Marked `electron-window-state` as external so esbuild doesn’t bundle it, avoiding dynamic `require` errors.

**Usage**
- Launch headful Weibo run via:
  - default headful: `node scripts/start-headful.mjs --profile weibo_fresh --url https://weibo.com`
  - explicitly headless: add `--headless` (flag only, no “false”).

**Status**
- Floating panel now tolerates `console.log` failures, logs to `/tmp/webauto-floating-panel.log` if needed, and the window can be resized with persisted geometry. rebuilding succeeded. Consider restarting the launcher to pick up the new floating panel build.
